1
00:00:00,030 --> 00:00:02,950
[Please tell me if I did anything wrong.]

2
00:00:05,640 --> 00:00:07,410
But no matter what happens,

3
00:00:07,430 --> 00:00:09,230
I hope your friend

4
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:11,460
can speak his mind.

5
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:43,300
You drank yesterday.

6
00:00:44,310 --> 00:00:45,770
No matter how much I drank,

7
00:00:46,270 --> 00:00:48,000
I couldn't get back what I lost.

8
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:50,670
You go rest over there.

9
00:00:50,690 --> 00:00:51,750
I'll handle it.

10
00:00:56,720 --> 00:00:57,420
Junjia.

11
00:00:59,520 --> 00:00:59,950
She...

12
00:01:01,060 --> 00:01:02,720
She was taken by someone else.

13
00:01:04,390 --> 00:01:07,450
Didn't you say you wanted
to observe for a while longer?

14
00:01:08,530 --> 00:01:08,960
Yeah.

15
00:01:09,420 --> 00:01:10,960
I observed for a week,

16
00:01:11,590 --> 00:01:13,570
and finally she got together
with someone else.

17
00:01:13,570 --> 00:01:14,600
One week?

18
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:18,070
You haven't even expressed your love yet,
right?

19
00:01:18,070 --> 00:01:19,070
What are you crying for?

20
00:01:19,070 --> 00:01:20,240
You know nothing.

21
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:22,930
A week's observation still means love.

22
00:01:22,930 --> 00:01:24,460
I stayed with her every day,

23
00:01:24,980 --> 00:01:26,310
buying her breakfast,

24
00:01:26,610 --> 00:01:28,220
carrying her things,

25
00:01:28,820 --> 00:01:30,820
and telling her all the jokes I know.

26
00:01:31,690 --> 00:01:33,220
But finally, she just said,

27
00:01:33,860 --> 00:01:36,320
"The person I like expressed
his love to me."

28
00:01:38,020 --> 00:01:39,590
Then I had nothing.

29
00:01:44,370 --> 00:01:45,330
But

30
00:01:46,070 --> 00:01:48,300
you had known she liked someone else.

31
00:01:48,870 --> 00:01:50,470
Why did you still like her?

32
00:01:50,470 --> 00:01:51,910
Liking her is my business.

33
00:01:51,910 --> 00:01:53,640
What does it have to do with her?

34
00:01:55,009 --> 00:01:57,009
I'm fine even though I was rejected.

35
00:02:01,020 --> 00:02:02,520
I really regret

36
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:04,120
not telling her my feelings.

37
00:02:07,180 --> 00:02:07,950
Welcome...

38
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,710
Wei, help me out.

39
00:02:13,730 --> 00:02:14,330
Excuse me.

40
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:16,430
Do you have

41
00:02:16,430 --> 00:02:17,890
another part-timer here?

42
00:02:19,710 --> 00:02:21,040
Could I know where he is?

43
00:02:22,570 --> 00:02:24,400
You mean Junjia?

44
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:27,610
He...

45
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:30,910
He...

46
00:02:30,910 --> 00:02:32,710
He got off work early today.

47
00:02:37,350 --> 00:02:38,150
Thanks.

48
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:02,370
I bought you a new strap.

49
00:03:02,850 --> 00:03:04,050
Change it if you want.

50
00:03:34,410 --> 00:03:35,079
Jiayi.

51
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:38,220
Jiayi.

52
00:03:39,230 --> 00:03:39,900
Jiayi.

53
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:50,600
Are you okay?

54
00:03:50,980 --> 00:03:51,820
What's up?

55
00:03:54,590 --> 00:03:56,450
You still care about me after all.

56
00:03:57,130 --> 00:03:58,079
Let go.

57
00:03:59,170 --> 00:04:01,170
I said I would never let you go again.

58
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:05,920
Senior.

59
00:04:05,940 --> 00:04:07,270
I won't let you go again.

60
00:04:08,780 --> 00:04:10,390
No matter what happens,

61
00:04:11,450 --> 00:04:12,660
I will always find you

62
00:04:13,650 --> 00:04:15,110
in the midst of the crowds.

63
00:04:16,149 --> 00:04:16,820
Jiayi.

64
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,360
Jiayi.

65
00:04:23,910 --> 00:04:24,680
It's okay.

66
00:04:26,690 --> 00:04:27,460
It's okay.

67
00:04:30,370 --> 00:04:31,210
It's okay.

68
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:32,710
It's okay.

69
00:04:34,250 --> 00:04:36,050
But why did you let me go?

70
00:04:40,510 --> 00:04:41,340
I'm sorry.

71
00:04:42,780 --> 00:04:44,380
As long as you don't let me go,

72
00:04:44,780 --> 00:04:46,180
I won't let you go either.

73
00:04:54,260 --> 00:04:55,220
Tell me.

74
00:04:55,370 --> 00:04:56,520
What did I do wrong?

75
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:57,430
You did nothing wrong.

76
00:04:57,430 --> 00:04:59,030
Then why are you avoiding me?

77
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:01,600
Because I fell for you.

78
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:10,490
[Smile After Tears]

79
00:06:10,710 --> 00:06:13,870
[Sixth fret: Love never plays
by the rules]

80
00:06:20,330 --> 00:06:21,900
Because I fell for you.

81
00:06:54,510 --> 00:06:55,640
Just for a moment.

82
00:07:28,030 --> 00:07:29,230
Give me some time.

83
00:07:29,970 --> 00:07:32,570
I will definitely give you
the answer you want.

84
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:58,750
Judging from recent conditions,

85
00:07:58,750 --> 00:08:00,810
I found the tumor is much more stable.

86
00:08:00,910 --> 00:08:02,640
As long as you keep
taking your medicine on time

87
00:08:02,640 --> 00:08:04,110
and staying happy,

88
00:08:04,130 --> 00:08:06,200
there's no need to worry too much.

89
00:08:31,810 --> 00:08:34,140
It's the first time
I've seen you so happy.

90
00:08:34,659 --> 00:08:35,490
Really?

91
00:08:38,010 --> 00:08:39,309
Otherwise, when would you

92
00:08:39,309 --> 00:08:41,169
go out of your way to text your dad?

93
00:08:44,550 --> 00:08:46,450
How could you peek at my phone?

94
00:08:52,590 --> 00:08:54,030
Did you meet someone?

95
00:08:58,270 --> 00:08:59,410
Now, you

96
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:02,010
are just like your dad.

97
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,330
You've become very gentle.

98
00:09:06,370 --> 00:09:07,680
He used to be cool

99
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:08,510
and reserved.

100
00:09:09,810 --> 00:09:11,140
It wasn't until he met me

101
00:09:12,250 --> 00:09:13,260
that I realized

102
00:09:14,050 --> 00:09:15,580
he was a very gentle person.

103
00:09:17,490 --> 00:09:19,050
Only then did I understand

104
00:09:19,980 --> 00:09:21,750
that love can change a person.

105
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:37,670
But, Mom,

106
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:40,810
do I really have

107
00:09:41,970 --> 00:09:43,970
the right to love someone right now?

108
00:09:48,620 --> 00:09:50,220
Why do you have to ask yourself

109
00:09:50,220 --> 00:09:52,280
if you have the right to love someone?

110
00:09:57,130 --> 00:09:59,570
Life is short.

111
00:09:59,870 --> 00:10:01,320
Now that time is limited,

112
00:10:01,660 --> 00:10:03,280
there is more reason to love.

113
00:10:03,470 --> 00:10:05,820
[Jiayi]

114
00:10:05,710 --> 00:10:06,710
Regret

115
00:10:06,730 --> 00:10:09,130
is often not about
loving the wrong person,

116
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:12,270
but about never having loved at all.

117
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:38,520
[Guitar Friends]

118
00:10:49,580 --> 00:10:50,920
Long time no see.

119
00:10:51,980 --> 00:10:53,010
Here to restock?

120
00:10:53,780 --> 00:10:55,150
We have new fretboard oil

121
00:10:55,150 --> 00:10:56,220
on the left shelf.

122
00:10:56,410 --> 00:10:57,610
Take a look yourself.

123
00:10:58,910 --> 00:11:01,040
I want to buy a guitar today.

124
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:04,150
We just got two new models.

125
00:11:04,490 --> 00:11:05,990
Come on, let me show you.

126
00:11:08,340 --> 00:11:09,300
Do you have the kind

127
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:10,670
with a clean tone

128
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:12,130
and an HSS configuration?

129
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:14,240
Try this one.

130
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:18,120
Its pickup configuration is standard.

131
00:11:18,170 --> 00:11:19,410
It feels a bit stiff,

132
00:11:19,410 --> 00:11:21,210
but the sustain is quite stable.

133
00:11:22,910 --> 00:11:24,580
This one feels a bit stiff.

134
00:11:26,010 --> 00:11:27,210
I hope its overtone layers

135
00:11:27,210 --> 00:11:28,610
can perform a bit better.

136
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:30,280
And

137
00:11:30,700 --> 00:11:32,290
I hope it's durable.

138
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:33,960
Okay.

139
00:11:35,820 --> 00:11:37,260
Then, try this one.

140
00:11:37,860 --> 00:11:39,910
Its resonance is more delicate,

141
00:11:40,390 --> 00:11:42,050
and the grip feels more solid.

142
00:11:47,350 --> 00:11:49,600
But it's more expensive.

143
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:51,070
I rarely see students

144
00:11:51,070 --> 00:11:52,730
choose a guitar at this level.

145
00:11:53,410 --> 00:11:55,010
Are you giving it to someone?

146
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:00,270
This one.

147
00:12:02,050 --> 00:12:02,830
Okay.

148
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:04,520
We have a free engraving service.

149
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:05,320
Do you need it?

150
00:12:07,570 --> 00:12:08,170
Yes.

151
00:12:11,790 --> 00:12:12,260
Here,

152
00:12:12,260 --> 00:12:14,260
write down what you want to engrave.

153
00:12:59,870 --> 00:13:02,470
Seems like he is a very important person
to you.

154
00:13:04,910 --> 00:13:06,710
Cherish this bond.

155
00:13:10,950 --> 00:13:12,050
That's okay.

156
00:13:14,050 --> 00:13:14,760
Thanks.

157
00:13:46,330 --> 00:13:48,830
[Senior He]

158
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:53,630
Hello.

159
00:13:53,630 --> 00:13:55,660
Are you free this weekend?

160
00:13:56,260 --> 00:13:57,100
Yeah.

161
00:13:57,830 --> 00:13:58,530
What's up?

162
00:13:58,930 --> 00:14:00,930
I want to talk to you about something

163
00:14:01,300 --> 00:14:02,800
about the two of us.

164
00:14:05,870 --> 00:14:06,510
Okay.

165
00:15:10,570 --> 00:15:11,370
Senior.

166
00:15:11,390 --> 00:15:12,560
Did you notice?

167
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:15,750
We didn't hit any red lights today.

168
00:15:18,270 --> 00:15:19,240
Today

169
00:15:19,630 --> 00:15:21,130
must be a lucky day.

170
00:15:25,660 --> 00:15:28,500
[Xpark Aquarium]

171
00:15:34,030 --> 00:15:34,660
I've bought tickets.

172
00:15:34,660 --> 00:15:35,200
Let's go.

173
00:15:35,530 --> 00:15:36,300
I can't remember the last time

174
00:15:36,300 --> 00:15:38,270
I went to the aquarium.

175
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:39,870
I'm so looking forward to it.

176
00:15:40,650 --> 00:15:41,710
Then, today,

177
00:15:41,830 --> 00:15:43,840
I'll make up for all your happiness.

178
00:15:46,410 --> 00:15:47,040
Let's go.

179
00:16:10,900 --> 00:16:11,930
Penguins.

180
00:16:12,270 --> 00:16:13,120
Look,

181
00:16:13,830 --> 00:16:14,980
so cute.

182
00:17:02,480 --> 00:17:03,480
Pretty, right?

183
00:17:05,650 --> 00:17:06,800
Senior He,

184
00:17:07,420 --> 00:17:09,190
don't you think it's weird?

185
00:17:10,319 --> 00:17:12,579
Fish have a memory of only seven seconds.

186
00:17:13,130 --> 00:17:15,109
They live in the same space

187
00:17:15,859 --> 00:17:17,770
and clearly know each other,

188
00:17:17,810 --> 00:17:19,339
yet act like strangers.

189
00:17:20,500 --> 00:17:23,040
Like acquaintances but also strangers.

190
00:17:24,619 --> 00:17:26,720
My family used to keep fish.

191
00:17:27,450 --> 00:17:28,860
One male fish

192
00:17:29,150 --> 00:17:31,010
would mate with many female fish.

193
00:17:31,100 --> 00:17:34,340
Although I saw many baby fish born,

194
00:17:35,170 --> 00:17:36,470
I always felt

195
00:17:36,580 --> 00:17:39,090
fish are the scummiest creatures,

196
00:17:40,050 --> 00:17:42,690
forgetting the ones they once loved.

197
00:17:44,510 --> 00:17:46,920
Some animals are just born to reproduce.

198
00:17:47,690 --> 00:17:49,220
You can't call them scummy.

199
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:51,280
I know.

200
00:17:52,030 --> 00:17:53,670
But I have a question.

201
00:17:54,450 --> 00:17:55,590
Is love

202
00:17:55,640 --> 00:17:57,500
really only worth seven seconds?

203
00:17:59,570 --> 00:18:01,390
I once read a book

204
00:18:01,910 --> 00:18:02,940
that said,

205
00:18:03,580 --> 00:18:06,210
"loving only once in a lifetime

206
00:18:06,620 --> 00:18:07,790
is happiness".

207
00:18:09,790 --> 00:18:12,230
Some animals also love only once,

208
00:18:13,090 --> 00:18:15,360
like the penguins we just saw.

209
00:18:16,620 --> 00:18:18,480
They love only once in a lifetime.

210
00:18:19,190 --> 00:18:20,260
So do some fish.

211
00:18:20,470 --> 00:18:23,070
Like the French angelfish.

212
00:18:23,650 --> 00:18:25,760
They live,

213
00:18:26,460 --> 00:18:27,330
travel,

214
00:18:28,100 --> 00:18:29,400
and even hunt in pairs.

215
00:18:35,510 --> 00:18:36,440
I think

216
00:18:37,290 --> 00:18:38,470
true love

217
00:18:39,210 --> 00:18:40,410
is not seven seconds,

218
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:42,880
nor a lifetime,

219
00:18:43,530 --> 00:18:45,790
but every moment you spend with someone.

220
00:18:47,370 --> 00:18:48,440
Just like now.

221
00:19:00,030 --> 00:19:03,450
[Heartbeats and Underwater Shadows]

222
00:19:10,780 --> 00:19:11,840
What are you doing?

223
00:19:12,560 --> 00:19:13,890
You'll fall in a second.

224
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:14,990
No, I won't.

225
00:19:19,080 --> 00:19:20,150
What?

226
00:19:20,180 --> 00:19:21,180
Nothing.

227
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:24,970
Careful.

228
00:19:29,180 --> 00:19:29,780
See?

229
00:19:30,450 --> 00:19:31,650
I told you you'd fall.

230
00:19:33,170 --> 00:19:34,550
With you holding me,

231
00:19:34,710 --> 00:19:35,950
I won't fall.

232
00:19:51,660 --> 00:19:52,460
Okay.

233
00:19:52,820 --> 00:19:53,750
What do you mean?

234
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:56,430
Wait for me here.

235
00:19:57,220 --> 00:19:58,250
I'll be right back.

236
00:19:58,250 --> 00:19:59,280
So mysterious.

237
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:26,000
[Alarm clock]

238
00:20:28,360 --> 00:20:28,670
[Alarm clock]

239
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:41,850
[Good night.] [Good morning.]

240
00:20:58,920 --> 00:21:01,530
Let's review electromagnetic waves.

241
00:21:02,390 --> 00:21:04,760
A magnetic field that changes over time

242
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:06,890
generates an electric field.

243
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:10,430
So, under mutual induction,

244
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:12,030
a regularly changing electric field

245
00:21:12,030 --> 00:21:14,470
is generated in space.

246
00:21:16,760 --> 00:21:19,610
[Electromagnetic in a vacuum]

247
00:21:18,070 --> 00:21:19,510
After we got together,

248
00:21:19,690 --> 00:21:21,260
life went on.

249
00:21:21,930 --> 00:21:24,060
I still studied hard.

250
00:21:31,990 --> 00:21:33,190
Maybe it is

251
00:21:33,190 --> 00:21:35,120
because you're in your senior year

252
00:21:35,550 --> 00:21:38,460
that club activities are suspended
for a few days.

253
00:21:43,810 --> 00:21:46,210
I still have to work part-time
every night.

254
00:22:13,930 --> 00:22:14,630
Junjia.

255
00:22:15,980 --> 00:22:17,020
Go back and rest.

256
00:22:18,030 --> 00:22:20,230
I'll go back after I finish cleaning up.

257
00:22:21,530 --> 00:22:22,300
I prepared this for you.

258
00:22:22,300 --> 00:22:23,240
Your favorite.

259
00:22:23,520 --> 00:22:24,650
Take it back and eat.

260
00:22:25,990 --> 00:22:27,490
Just take it.

261
00:22:29,740 --> 00:22:30,810
Hurry up and rest.

262
00:22:30,810 --> 00:22:31,600
Here,

263
00:22:31,710 --> 00:22:32,840
we two will clean up.

264
00:22:40,020 --> 00:22:41,500
And let me tell you,

265
00:22:41,620 --> 00:22:43,290
Wei is in love again.

266
00:22:44,150 --> 00:22:45,910
I will always remember

267
00:22:45,950 --> 00:22:47,520
that smile of love.

268
00:22:53,170 --> 00:22:54,100
It was just like

269
00:22:54,290 --> 00:22:56,330
the first touch of hands.

270
00:22:57,100 --> 00:22:59,230
And the first time you worried about me

271
00:22:59,840 --> 00:23:01,910
when I first met you.

272
00:23:04,750 --> 00:23:05,880
If it hurts,

273
00:23:06,510 --> 00:23:07,770
why didn't you tell me?

274
00:23:10,050 --> 00:23:12,050
The first time you held my hand.

275
00:23:16,760 --> 00:23:18,130
The first time

276
00:23:18,330 --> 00:23:19,690
you embraced me.

277
00:23:20,990 --> 00:23:22,030
It's fine.

278
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:26,170
And

279
00:23:27,230 --> 00:23:29,170
the first time you turned around.

280
00:23:30,500 --> 00:23:31,340
Thanks.

281
00:23:37,810 --> 00:23:38,980
He Yankai.

282
00:23:39,650 --> 00:23:41,180
Didn't you say

283
00:23:41,420 --> 00:23:42,780
true love

284
00:23:43,180 --> 00:23:44,380
is not seven seconds,

285
00:23:45,830 --> 00:23:47,350
nor a lifetime,

286
00:23:47,790 --> 00:23:50,300
but every moment you spend with someone?

287
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:52,190
But

288
00:23:52,960 --> 00:23:54,860
you were the short seven seconds

289
00:23:55,160 --> 00:23:58,130
after turning around and letting me go.

290
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:07,870
[Preview of the Next Episode]

291
00:24:05,110 --> 00:24:06,440
In terms of many things,

292
00:24:06,460 --> 00:24:08,120
we don't have a second chance.

293
00:24:12,450 --> 00:24:13,410
Are you

294
00:24:13,410 --> 00:24:14,510
Jiayi?

295
00:24:17,370 --> 00:24:18,580
Do you know

